==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}} {{term|trigonometria|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|τρίγωνον||triangle|lang=grc}} + {{term|-metria||-metry|lang=la}}.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|~|trigonometries}}

# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} The branch of [[mathematics]] that deals with the [[relationship]]s between the [[side]]s and the [[angle]]s of [[triangle]]s and the [[calculation]]s based on them, particularly the [[trigonometric function]]s.

